The evidence with the title 'The worst mistake in the History Of The Human Race ... ' says May 1, 1999  ... For most of our history we supported ourselves by hunting and gathering : we hunted wild animals and foraged for wild plants. It's a life  ... For instance , the average time devoted each week to obtaining food is only 12 to 19 hours for one group of Bushmen, 14 hours or less for the Hadza nomads of Tanzania. 
